content.description: Mantle above of the first bolt and climb to the top of the ‘Pack Rat Pillar’. Follow a crack right, then left, to the anchors.
content.protection: Pro to 1", 2 bolts, and a 2 bolt anchor.
content.location: It is on the left side of the crag behind a pine tree.

content.description: A bouldery start leads to a fun roof. It is worth stickclipping the first bolt and anchoring your belayer with a cam in the cave.
content.protection: Pro to 0.5”, 3 bolts, and a 2 bolt anchor.
content.location: It is on the right side of the crag next to the cave.

content.description: Climb the finger crack to a rest before entering the bouldery overhang.
content.protection: Pro to 1”, 2 bolts, and a 2 bolt anchor.
content.location: It is in the center of the wall.

climbs.name: Insane Rush
climbs.fa: Greg Miller, Francy Lang, James Kessler 9/2020

content.description: Insane Rush is named for the IPA enjoyed after the FA. Climb onto a ramp, follow two bolts protecting moves between slopey rails, above the second bolt move left to the right-facing corner, get creative placing gear. Stem your way up to steep blocky terrain and the anchor.
content.protection: Pro to 1”, 2 bolts, and a 2 bolt anchor.
content.location:
It is in between “

Moose Track

” and “

.”
